<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="285" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,420,735]" pageId="14" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis box="[199,339,529,554]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="285">Description.</emphasis>
Internal sac everted dorsally in lateral view. DLL largest in the bladders; VA same as large as B and DA; A exist. VLR, BLR and VB not exist.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,420,735]" pageId="14" pageNumber="285">VA short triangular everted dorsally. DA everted dorsally. B roundly swollen right laterally, with well sclerotized spines, which are forming an oblong band. DLL swollen dorsally, covered with numerous well-sclerotized spines, which are a forming band. Flagellum well short, curved and formed S shape. Medial tooth long, gently curved right ventro-laterally, gently tapered at apex.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
